ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This was an excellent, though intense, investigation of the notion of identity in the Age of Enlightenment with a heavy dose of literary criticism thrown in. I encourage anyone with an interest in this subject to take it. The course was, furthermore, very open to student input and thus ideal for graduate students whose research interests coincide with it.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Though my research interests are still developing, this course has vastly expanded the critical corpus that will serve me as I begin graduate work. Though I am primarily interested in the Middle Ages and Renaissance, this course has led me to consider these periods in the context of their relationship to the Enlightenment as well.
